text.Taxonomy and naming:
Thelymitra grandiflora was first formally described in 1882 by Robert Fitzgerald and the description was published in The Gardeners' Chronicle.The specific epithet (grandiflora) is derived from the Latin words grandis meaning "large" and flos, genitive floris meaning flower".In 2014, Robert Bates described two subspecies and the names have been accepted by the World Checklist of Selected Plant Families:

Thelymitra grandiflora subsp. grandiflora;
Thelymitra grandiflora subsp. exposa.
